191.1	Montreal	Montreal	As of February 2012, Statistics Canada identifies Montreal's Census Metropolitan Area (CMA) (land area 4,259 square kilometres (1,644 sq mi)) as Canada's second most populous with an estimated metropolitan area population of 3,824,221 and a population of 1,886,481 in the "agglomeration" of Montreal, which includes all of the municipalities on the island of Montreal. The city of Montreal proper had a population of 1,649,519 as of the 2011 census.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/VuedeMontreal.jpg/300px-VuedeMontreal.jpg
